For what it's worth (which admittedly may not be much) I use a simple
version of this idea to generate magic cookies for my X server.  My X
sessions are started by invoking this shell function:

x () 
{ 
    local x=$( (cat .Xauthority; ps augx) | md5 );
    ( echo add :0 . $x;
    echo add $HOSTNAME:0 . $x ) | xauth;
    xinit -- -auth .Xauthority;
}

Just an idea that someone might find marginally useful...
